  "summary": "Invoking \"go bug\" follows symlinks in predictable temporary filenames in cmd/go",
  "details": "The \"go bug\" command writes to two files with predictable names in the system temporary directory (for example, \"/tmp\").\n\nAn attacker with access to the temporary directory can create a symlink in one of these names, causing \"go bug\" to overwrite the target of the symlink.",
